HEADWORD: avant-courier
<hw>a*vant"-cou`ri*er</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>avant</ets> before + <ets>courrier</ets>. See <er>Avaunt</er>, and
<er>Courier</er>.]</ety> <def>A person dispatched before another person
or company, to give notice of his or their approach.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

